    "IMMIGRATION BILL BEFORE THE HOUSE Educational Qualification for Incoming Aliens Discussed GENERAL Explains That the Measure Codifies Existing Laws Proposes Exclusion of Anarchists Mr Williams An nounces Intention of Amending on the bill He entered Into an elabor ate explanation of the provisions of the measure and an exhaustive discussion of the subject of Immigration He said the bare statement that the number of immigrants received into the United States during the past eighty years equals more than one quarter of the present population and that more thun one half nearly two thirds has hem received In the last thirty years presents In a concrete form the magni tude of the Immigration problem In the years gone by this constant stream of Immigrants he said has been welcome d to our shores partly as a valuable contribution to the brawn and brain that peopled the prairies of the West and transformed them into the rich and powerful States that delight our pride and strengthen our nation today nnfl partly because a large number of them came to escape wrong oppression and human suffering akin to that from which the Pilgrim Fathers fled when they crossed the ocean to found in"
